_header: God that made both day and night
_description: To the new moon — six lines

BLLan96.Transcription:
God that made boythe daye & neightThe mone shyne and the starres
                    soe lightThe holye sonne that shines bryghtKepe youe and save youe
                    from all ill sprytesGod hym seid bothe farre and neareThat bought vs
                    his blode soe deare
BLLan96.Editions:
Sparrow-Simpson,  W. 
             “On a Magical Roll Preserved in the British Museum.” 
             Journal of the British Archaeological Association
         48 (1892): 38-54: 45.
